                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1133: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-09T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 9, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 9—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Referring to the last sentence of my telegram No. 56, June 27,<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d184fn22">Not printed.</note> reliable sources of information
                    confirm the activity of Italian submarines in the Indian Ocean and Persian Gulf.
                    One was rammed recently at the entrance of the Gulf by a British destroyer and
                    another spotted in the Gulf is being searched for today by British bombing
                    planes. Steamer service between Iraq and India is uncertain and fully booked for
                    at least next 6 weeks. I am encouraging Americans evacuating through here to
                    travel when possible by air to Karachi and thence by rail to Bombay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
